                     </persName>
                  , with a certain knife, made of iron and steel, value 6 d. which he in his right hand then and there had and held, upon the left shoulder, forehead, nose and wrist of the said Duncan, did cut, flab, and penetrate, giving him with the knife aforesaid, divers mortal wounds, one on the left shoulder, of the length of six inches, and of the depth of one inch, one other wound on his forehead and nose of the length of two inches, and of the depth of one inch, of which he lingered till the 20th of November, and then died; and that the said 
